for you?

18:27.474 --> 18:30.169
[ Chuckles ] Not a thing.

18:30.290 --> 18:32.225
[ Cellphone chimes ]

18:38.564 --> 18:40.100
[ Touchscreen clicks ]

18:41.630 --> 18:43.765
Baz. He wants a meeting.

18:43.814 --> 18:46.182
About what?
[ Touchscreen clicking ]

18:46.506 --> 18:48.327
I don't know. He probably
wants that money back.

18:48.374 --> 18:50.528
Well, screw that.
It's ours.

18:50.942 --> 18:52.310
We gonna go?

18:52.398 --> 18:54.701
Not unarmed we're not.

18:56.549 --> 18:57.884
[ Buzzer ]

18:57.918 --> 18:59.716
[ Clank ]

19:06.443 --> 19:08.112
[ Gate closes ]

19:11.614 --> 19:13.645
[ Sighs ]

19:13.948 --> 19:15.417
How you been, Smurf?

19:15.520 --> 19:17.755
Do I need an attorney?

19:18.892 --> 19:20.247
I always figured
I'd find you

19:20.340 --> 19:22.919
in a place like this
sooner or later.

19:23.636 --> 19:25.538
Brought you something sweet.

19:29.092 --> 19:31.770
Somebody's been
robbing banks again.

19:32.468 --> 19:33.669
Lot of banks.

19:33.717 --> 19:35.497
Did you catch 'em?

19:35.799 --> 19:37.919
Not them. Him.

19:38.088 --> 19:39.895
One guy?

19:41.197 --> 19:43.130
Doesn't sound like anyone
I would know.

19:43.243 --> 19:44.950
I'm watching
the security footage,

19:44.998 --> 19:48.458
noticing how he walks, and he,
uh, he reminds me of someone.

19:48.981 --> 19:51.333
Yeah? Who's that?

19:52.020 --> 19:53.880
How is Pope?

19:54.844 --> 19:57.255
Pope's not robbing banks.

19:58.076 --> 19:59.545
Yeah.

19:59.757 --> 20:04.481
This guy... he robs six banks
in one day.

20:04.597 --> 20:06.599
And then just stopped.

20:06.716 --> 20:08.150
[ Pouring coffee ]

20:08.280 --> 20:10.016
It's curious.
[ Coffee pot clatters ]

20:10.182 --> 20:12.309
You wonder why.

20:12.845 --> 20:16.130
Maybe it's 'cause his mommy's
not there to kiss his booboos.

20:16.633 --> 20:18.919
Maybe Mommy's in jail.

20:20.014 --> 20:22.598
What do you want,
detective?

20:27.730 --> 20:30.032
It's time to cut a deal,
Janine.

20:30.238 --> 20:32.341
You're looking at 20 to life.

20:32.577 --> 20:33.802
I didn't do it.

20:33.885 --> 20:35.086
Well, of course not.

20:35.292 --> 20:39.177
[ Chuckles ] But I really
didn't do it.

20:41.303 --> 20:44.981
I took a peek at
the Grand Jury testimony.

20:45.511 --> 20:48.122
Doesn't look good
for your team.

20:49.685 --> 20:52.130
Give up your boys.

20:54.099 --> 20:57.177
You give 'em up,
you might get out of here

20:57.270 --> 20:58.466
before you're wearing Pampers

20:58.514 --> 21:00.794
and eating all your meals
out of a blender.

21:01.020 --> 21:04.888
♪♪

21:04.935 --> 21:08.833
♪♪

21:11.351 --> 21:14.194
♪♪

21:14.241 --> 21:16.241
♪♪

21:16.427 --> 21:19.630
[ Vehicle doors close ]

21:23.629 --> 21:25.531
[ Sighs ]

21:30.635 --> 21:33.004
[ Exhales deeply ]

21:38.077 --> 21:40.436
What's she doing here?

21:41.554 --> 21:44.835
What's she doing here?

21:45.983 --> 21:47.757
I asked her to be here.

21:48.020 --> 21:49.991
Same.

21:50.667 --> 21:52.452
Fine.

21:52.958 --> 21:55.060
Smurf gave J
her power of attorney,

21:55.147 --> 21:57.826
so now J controls
all the properties,

21:57.874 --> 21:59.460
the investments,
the bank accounts,

21:59.538 --> 22:02.835
this house, the title
to our cars, everything...

22:03.085 --> 22:06.460
Everything we earned
that she stole from us.

22:06.897 --> 22:08.741
She gave it all to J
because she didn't trust us...

22:08.774 --> 22:10.444
She doesn't trust you.

22:11.194 --> 22:13.733
Didn't trust us
to keep it safe for her.

22:13.979 --> 22:16.215
She thinks it's all hers,
not ours.

22:16.460 --> 22:18.684
What are you planning
on doing with it, J, huh?

22:18.827 --> 22:22.187
Everything we earned,
sweated over, bled for. Hmm?

22:22.311 --> 22:24.679
You planning on selling it,
like we all wanna do?

22:24.733 --> 22:25.835
Like you want to do.

22:25.889 --> 22:27.289
Oh, it is it just me?
Is that right?

22:27.336 --> 22:29.468
It's just me? I'm the only one
who wants to sell it?

22:29.895 --> 22:32.936
Pope? Deran? Craig?

22:33.490 --> 22:36.007
Why didn't you tell us what you
were planning on doing to Smurf?

22:36.054 --> 22:38.421
I didn't think you were strong
enough to go through with it.

22:38.522 --> 22:40.239
Strong enough?
Screw you, Baz.

22:40.272 --> 22:41.421
Yeah, strong enough.

22:41.469 --> 22:44.339
Little Deran running away every
time Mommy hurts his feelings.

22:44.511 --> 22:46.761
And you,
she looks at you sideways,

22:46.831 --> 22:48.182
you snort 10 grand
up your nose.

22:48.230 --> 22:50.858
Where's the rest of what I helped
you steal from those storage units?

22:50.905 --> 22:53.215
- It's safe. Don't worry about it.
- Yeah, but what was in those safes?

22:53.262 --> 22:54.683
Huh?
There were five of them.

22:54.731 --> 22:56.839
What, you think I'm holding out on you?
Yeah, I do.

22:56.907 --> 22:58.766
Who the hell do you think
you are, you little shit?

22:58.813 --> 23:01.706
She didn't trust you,
but she trusted me.

23:02.393 --> 23:04.307
And... and was she wrong?

23:04.463 --> 23:06.753
She's in prison
because of you, Baz!

23:06.988 --> 23:08.285
[ Scoffs ]

23:08.333 --> 23:11.170
- Deran: Hey! No, hey!
- Craig: Get off him!

23:11.253 --> 23:13.386
Hey, enough! Enough!
Shut up! Enough!

23:14.106 --> 23:15.643
Enough!

23:16.475 --> 23:20.245
♪♪

23:20.292 --> 23:23.995
♪♪

23:24.070 --> 23:25.405
Enough.

23:25.885 --> 23:29.761
♪♪

23:29.808 --> 23:33.589
♪♪

23:35.895 --> 23:39.762
♪♪

23:39.933 --> 23:43.575
♪♪

23:45.905 --> 23:49.372
♪♪

23:52.069 --> 23:54.571
[ Birds chirping ]

23:54.619 --> 23:57.255
[ Cellphone vibrating, ringing ]

23:57.303 --> 23:59.434
[ Inhales sharply ]

23:59.653 --> 24:01.021
[ Sighs ]

24:01.069 --> 24:03.239
[ Ring ]

24:03.503 --> 24:04.870
[ Exhales sharply ]

24:05.444 --> 24:06.946
[ Cellphone
continues vibrating ]

24:06.994 --> 24:09.411
[ Ring ]

24:10.503 --> 24:11.805
Hello?

24:11.853 --> 24:13.785
Automated female voice:
<i>You have a call from an inmate</i>

24:13.832 --> 24:16.206
<i>at San Marcos
Detention Facility.</i>

24:16.332 --> 24:17.904
- <i>To accept...</i>
- Yeah.

24:17.937 --> 24:19.590
Hey, baby.

24:19.768 --> 24:23.033
- Hi.
- [ Speaks indistinctly ]

24:23.253 --> 24:25.388
Yeah. Yeah, okay.

24:25.485 --> 24:30.356
- [ Speaks indistinctly ]
- Okay. Yeah, will do. Bye.

24:30.617 --> 24:32.509
[ Cellphone clatters ]

24:32.603 --> 24:36.400
[ Exhales sharply ]

24:36.789 --> 24:38.603
I gotta go and see Smurf.

24:39.158 --> 24:41.369
What? You're going now?

24:42.040 --> 24:45.043
I'll be here for
your graduation, I promise.

24:49.550 --> 24:51.685
[ Sighs ]

24:54.339 --> 24:55.775
[ Door closes ]

24:56.060 --> 24:57.561
Lena's not sleeping.

25:00.829 --> 25:03.599
Smurf's gone, Cath...

25:03.883 --> 25:06.470
I think she's afraid
that we're all gonna leave.

25:06.823 --> 25:09.353
And whose fault is it
she feels that way?

25:09.689 --> 25:12.040
Smurf's.

25:14.220 --> 25:16.462
I'm heading down to Mexico
tonight with Lucy.

25:16.580 --> 25:18.392
I'm gonna start
looking for a place.

25:18.596 --> 25:20.064
Are you okay
looking after Lena?

25:20.199 --> 25:22.068
How long
are you gonna be gone?

25:22.173 --> 25:25.037
I don't know, few days.
A week. I don't know.

25:28.009 --> 25:29.205
Hey, you don't want to do it,

25:29.253 --> 25:30.864
- I'll ask Allison. I got it, man.
- No. I'll do it.

25:30.911 --> 25:32.346
Okay.

25:35.257 --> 25:37.453
What are you planning to do
with Lena?

25:37.851 --> 25:40.653
What? Well, are you gonna take
her to Mexico with you and Lucy?

25:40.687 --> 25:43.148
It's none
of your goddamn business!

25:44.039 --> 25:46.359
And thanks for the support
last night, by the way!

25:46.414 --> 25:48.795
Standing there like a limp dick,
not saying shit to back me up!

25:48.828 --> 25:51.631
What is going to happen
to her, Baz?

25:51.804 --> 25:54.734
You gotta step up and be more
of a father to her.

25:54.874 --> 25:56.903
She's your kid.
You're never around.

25:56.936 --> 25:59.562
You don't seem to give a shit
that she's scared.

25:59.827 --> 26:01.296
You know what, you're right.

26:01.344 --> 26:04.945
She's my kid.
My kid, not yours.

26:06.176 --> 26:07.382
Get your shit together

26:07.430 --> 26:09.281
and support me in front
of the others.

26:10.249 --> 26:13.664
[ Engine starts, door closes ]

26:13.953 --> 26:17.484
♪♪

26:17.531 --> 26:20.523
♪♪

26:20.793 --> 26:23.046
[ Buzzer, gate clanks ]

26:24.548 --> 26:28.460
♪♪

26:29.749 --> 26:30.953
Hi, Baby.

26:31.046 --> 26:32.234
Hi.

26:32.295 --> 26:34.463
You look a little tired.

26:34.809 --> 26:36.109
How's Nicky?

26:36.311 --> 26:37.578
She's good, yeah.

26:37.641 --> 26:40.507
Her parents are flying in today
for our graduation.

26:42.085 --> 26:43.679
Are you graduating?

26:44.016 --> 26:45.421
Yeah.

26:46.052 --> 26:48.390
I'm gonna get you something
very expensive

26:48.476 --> 26:50.671
when I get out of here.

26:53.387 --> 26:55.757
You know who my father was?

26:57.476 --> 27:00.877
'Cause Baz said it was this
creepy, slick real estate guy

27:00.933 --> 27:02.468
that you had hanging around
the house.

27:02.539 --> 27:03.632
Baz is a prick.

27:03.680 --> 27:07.051
He's trying to upset you so he
can take advantage of you.

27:07.590 --> 27:09.445
Don't let him do that.

27:09.840 --> 27:12.554
[ Buzzer in distance ]

27:12.630 --> 27:14.332
♪♪

27:14.647 --> 27:17.585
Now tell Uncle Baz
he has to come see me.

27:17.784 --> 27:20.414
I've been trying to call him,
and he won't pick up.

27:21.442 --> 27:23.414
What if he won't come?

27:24.156 --> 27:26.325
Tell him I'm getting ready
to strike a deal.

27:26.453 --> 27:30.093
If not with him,
then Pearce.

27:30.141 --> 27:32.070
♪♪

27:32.264 --> 27:35.335
[ Children shouting playfully ]

27:35.635 --> 27:39.390
♪♪

27:39.437 --> 27:43.195
♪♪

27:45.645 --> 27:49.484
♪♪

27:49.531 --> 27:51.648
♪♪

27:52.218 --> 27:55.287
[ Truck alarm chirps ]

27:55.321 --> 27:57.539
♪♪

27:57.835 --> 27:59.904
Where have you been?

28:02.842 --> 28:04.429
[ Sighs ] Uh...

28:05.117 --> 28:07.648
I'm sorry. Smurf took a while
to come out.

28:07.696 --> 28:09.515
You were supposed to be here.

28:10.136 --> 28:12.406
I know. I'm sorry.

28:13.205 --> 28:16.242
Where are your parents?

28:17.015 --> 28:18.828
[ Sniffles ]

28:20.249 --> 28:23.398
They... they didn't come.

28:24.627 --> 28:30.017
They got me this. Corsage.

28:30.222 --> 28:32.904
[ Sniffles ] They missed
their connection in Honolulu

28:32.998 --> 28:36.201
and decided to stay because
they weren't gonna make it

28:36.287 --> 28:38.740
in time
for graduation anyway.

28:41.835 --> 28:45.178
Whatever. They're assholes.

28:46.763 --> 28:48.130
You still want to go?

28:48.274 --> 28:50.436
[ Sniffles ] Come on.

28:50.908 --> 28:53.740
I need to get high
and I'm out of coke.

28:55.251 --> 28:56.787
Let's go.

28:59.548 --> 29:02.357
[ Gate opens, buzzer ]

29:05.795 --> 29:07.154
[ Gate closes ]

29:13.446 --> 29:15.582
[ Gate closes in distance ]

29:23.930 --> 29:26.900
[ Receiver clatters ]

29:29.281 --> 29:32.107
It's a nice outfit.
What is that, polyester?

29:33.052 --> 29:35.888
It's a blend. Doesn't stain.

29:36.427 --> 29:38.498
Should come in handy.

29:39.404 --> 29:41.638
I put some money
in your commissary account.

29:41.928 --> 29:45.654
Wouldn't want you to run out of
toothpaste and tampons in here.

29:46.705 --> 29:49.173
You're always so thoughtful,

29:49.435 --> 29:53.904
but I'm way past tampons,
sweetie.

29:55.341 --> 29:57.043
What'd you do with all
the things

29:57.076 --> 29:59.052
from my storage unit?

30:00.482 --> 30:03.427
Took me a while to sort through,
but it's all safe.

30:03.783 --> 30:07.021
You make sure you share
with your brothers now, hmm?

30:07.253 --> 30:09.599
We both know how much
you like to take

30:09.654 --> 30:13.787
just a little bit more
than your fair share.

30:15.349 --> 30:17.974
Mm. Thanks, "Mom."
I'll try and remember that.

30:18.297 --> 30:20.279
What are you gonna do
with Lena?

30:21.319 --> 30:24.789
I can't take care
of your child from in here.

30:25.353 --> 30:27.232
We'll muddle through.

30:27.818 --> 30:31.396
Lena just wishes
you hadn't killed Javi.

30:32.443 --> 30:34.599
But I didn't kill Javi.

30:34.968 --> 30:37.938
You know that
better than anyone, Barry.

30:40.490 --> 30:43.060
J tells me Pearce came around.
That right?

30:43.202 --> 30:47.310
He did, and he had a very
interesting offer for me.

30:47.755 --> 30:50.068
You thinking
about taking it?

30:50.724 --> 30:53.404
It's not my style.

30:53.900 --> 30:57.490
Never trust an outsider to do
the right thing.

31:01.833 --> 31:04.279
So why am I here?

31:05.662 --> 31:08.414
What do you
hear from Cath?

31:09.877 --> 31:11.951
What?

31:13.319 --> 31:16.005
Ask Pope. Pope knows.

31:16.588 --> 31:19.365
♪♪

31:19.859 --> 31:23.130
Broke poor Pope's heart
when Cath chose you.

31:23.489 --> 31:25.891
♪♪

31:26.198 --> 31:28.974
I don't think he ever
got over it.

31:29.768 --> 31:31.404
Can you blame him?

31:33.291 --> 31:36.677
His own brother
takes his girl.

31:38.911 --> 31:42.037
You think
you see things clearly?

31:43.454 --> 31:45.201
You don't.

31:46.281 --> 31:49.435
You think you have
Pope's loyalty...

31:51.529 --> 31:53.185
But you don't.

31:53.670 --> 31:55.529
I do.

31:56.744 --> 31:58.732
Pope loves you.

31:59.560 --> 32:01.576
And he loved Catherine.

32:02.748 --> 32:07.560
But Pope will always
love me more.

32:07.608 --> 32:11.388
♪♪

32:11.435 --> 32:14.919
♪♪

32:16.888 --> 32:18.404
[ Sighs ]

32:18.652 --> 32:21.099
[ Receiver clatters ]

32:24.156 --> 32:27.126
[ Footsteps depart ]

32:27.159 --> 32:29.261
♪♪

32:29.295 --> 32:32.060
[ Shower running ]

32:32.298 --> 32:36.005
♪♪

32:36.052 --> 32:39.638
♪♪

32:42.143 --> 32:44.211
♪♪

32:44.292 --> 32:46.560
[ Cellphone rings ]

32:48.180 --> 32:49.648
♪♪

32:49.964 --> 32:52.261
[ Ring ]

32:52.373 --> 32:54.953
♪♪

32:55.054 --> 32:57.625
[ Ring ]

32:57.673 --> 33:01.375
♪♪

33:01.743 --> 33:03.914
[ Ring ]

33:04.062 --> 33:07.868
♪♪

33:10.036 --> 33:12.430
[ Ring ]

33:13.848 --> 33:15.718
Automated female voice: <i>You
have a call from an inmate...</i>

33:15.765 --> 33:17.166
[ Cellphone beeps ]

33:17.310 --> 33:18.961
Baz knows.

33:19.030 --> 33:21.008
♪♪

33:21.218 --> 33:23.211
He'll be coming for you.

33:24.207 --> 33:25.441
[ Receiver clatters ]

33:25.717 --> 33:29.571
♪♪

33:29.619 --> 33:31.274
[ Cellphone thuds ]

33:31.322 --> 33:34.157
♪♪

33:39.931 --> 33:41.501
[ Engine turns off ]

33:48.440 --> 33:50.509
[ Vehicle passes ]

33:50.779 --> 33:54.849
[ Kegs clatter ]

33:55.187 --> 33:56.866
- Hey.
- You heard from Baz?

33:57.054 --> 33:58.937
What? Why?

33:59.312 --> 34:01.214
Shit might be going down.

34:01.412 --> 34:03.351
What shit?

34:04.233 --> 34:05.968
[ Sighs ]

34:08.172 --> 34:11.092
If something happens to me,
will you look after Lena?

34:14.827 --> 34:16.359
Hey.

34:17.462 --> 34:19.109
I need an answer.

34:20.702 --> 34:23.138
If something happens to me,
will you take care Lena?

34:23.186 --> 34:24.719
Yes or no?

34:27.264 --> 34:29.116
Yeah, of course.

34:29.357 --> 34:32.804
♪♪

34:43.933 --> 34:45.034
[ Exhales slowly ]

34:46.221 --> 34:48.018
[ Inhales, grunts ]

34:48.179 --> 34:49.780
What are we doing here?

34:50.167 --> 34:53.083
I left a jacket at Mindy's house
two years ago.

34:53.495 --> 34:55.219
She says she doesn't have it,

34:55.635 --> 34:58.706
but I saw her wearing it
at a party on Snapchat.

34:59.182 --> 35:00.721
Two years ago?

35:01.213 --> 35:02.729
I want it back.

35:02.863 --> 35:04.164
[ Truck door opens ]

35:04.792 --> 35:06.494
[ Truck door closes ]

35:12.424 --> 35:15.292
[ Glass shatters ]

35:15.542 --> 35:17.557
Whoa, don't...
Don't touch anything.

35:19.210 --> 35:20.776
Thanks.

35:27.118 --> 35:28.119
[ Panting ]

35:28.237 --> 35:31.299
[ Gasps ] Oh, hey! Hi, Jasper!

35:31.929 --> 35:33.479
Okay.

35:45.236 --> 35:48.292
I knew it. Bitch.

35:49.635 --> 35:51.635
Okay. Let's go.

35:57.854 --> 35:59.487
Nicky.

35:59.972 --> 36:03.571
♪♪

36:03.618 --> 36:06.970
♪♪

36:10.279 --> 36:12.314
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

36:12.629 --> 36:16.521
♪♪

36:17.701 --> 36:21.482
[ Panting ]

36:23.529 --> 36:25.255
Okay, now can we go?

36:25.427 --> 36:27.154
[ Exhales sharply ] No.

36:27.311 --> 36:29.459
Mindy's mom is a buyer
for Saks.

36:29.630 --> 36:31.548
She has all kinds
of cool shit.

36:31.724 --> 36:34.218
We're gonna steal it all.

36:43.194 --> 36:45.796
[ Gears shift,
engine turns off ]

36:48.465 --> 36:51.668
[ Airplane flying overhead ]

36:54.571 --> 36:58.287
♪♪

36:58.334 --> 37:02.021
♪♪

37:04.581 --> 37:08.271
♪♪

37:08.318 --> 37:12.146
♪♪

37:14.296 --> 37:18.092
♪♪

37:18.595 --> 37:20.545
[ Keys jangle, lock turns ]

37:20.764 --> 37:24.396
♪♪

37:24.443 --> 37:28.256
♪♪

37:28.443 --> 37:32.115
♪♪

37:32.976 --> 37:36.606
♪♪

37:39.568 --> 37:40.842
[ Clip clicks ]

37:41.295 --> 37:44.165
♪♪

37:44.488 --> 37:48.693
[ Clicking ]

37:49.544 --> 37:53.412
♪♪

37:55.832 --> 37:58.014
[ Engine revs ]

37:58.732 --> 38:00.334
[ Engine turns off ]

38:00.504 --> 38:04.295
♪♪

38:04.342 --> 38:07.865
♪♪

38:08.005 --> 38:11.896
♪♪

38:12.036 --> 38:15.803
♪♪

38:15.850 --> 38:19.529
♪♪

38:19.874 --> 38:23.771
♪♪

38:23.818 --> 38:27.686
♪♪

38:28.002 --> 38:31.662
♪♪

38:31.709 --> 38:35.561
♪♪

38:37.186 --> 38:39.428
[ Voice breaks ]
She didn't suffer.

38:43.019 --> 38:46.136
We thought she was...

38:47.497 --> 38:49.399
talking to the cops.

38:50.821 --> 38:53.183
[ Breathing deeply ]

